Vice President Mike Pence spoke with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan to discuss the security situation in Afghanistan, including recent ceasefires initiated by the Afghan Government and the Taliban. Pence reiterated the US and international commitment to support the Afghan government and security forces. He also commended Ghani's efforts to make progress on a negotiated settlement to the conflict in Afghanistan, as outlined in President Trump's South Asia strategy. They also discussed the importance of holding democratic elections and political inclusion for the long-term stability of the Kabul government.